## Fixing Memory Leaks in Long-Running Node.js Processes

### 1. Identify the leak

- **`--inspect` + Chrome DevTools** — run `node --inspect app.js`, open `chrome://inspect`, take heap snapshots over time, compare allocations.
- **`process.memoryUsage()`** — log `rss` and `heapUsed` periodically to confirm growth.
- **`clinic doctor`** / `clinic heap` — automated diagnostics: `npx clinic doctor -- node app.js`.

### 2. Common causes & fixes

| Cause | Fix |
|-------|-----|
| **Unbounded caches/maps** | Use an LRU cache (`lru-cache` package) or `WeakMap`/`WeakRef` |
| **Event listener accumulation** | Always call `removeListener`/`off` when done; watch for "MaxListenersExceeded" warnings |
| **Closures capturing large scopes** | Nullify references you no longer need; avoid closing over large buffers |
| **Uncleared timers** | `clearInterval`/`clearTimeout` when the owner is destroyed |
| **Streams not consumed/destroyed** | Always handle `error` events; call `stream.destroy()` on abort |
| **Global variables / module-level arrays** | Avoid pushing to module-scope collections without eviction |
| **Forgotten Promises** | Ensure all promises settle; unresolved promises hold their closure tree |

### 3. Heap snapshot comparison (most effective technique)

```js
// Take snapshots programmatically
const v8 = require('v8');
const fs = require('fs');

function dumpHeap(tag) {
  const file = `/tmp/heap-${tag}-${Date.now()}.heapsnapshot`;
  v8.writeHeapSnapshot(file);
  console.log(`Heap snapshot: ${file}`);
}
```

Take one snapshot early, another after suspected growth, then load both in DevTools → **Comparison** view. Sort by **"# Delta"** to find object types accumulating.

### 4. Quick checklist

```js
// ❌ Leak: listener added every request, never removed
app.on('request', (req) => {
  someEmitter.on('data', handler); // accumulates!
});

// ✅ Fix: remove when done
app.on('request', (req) => {
  someEmitter.on('data', handler);
  req.on('close', () => someEmitter.off('data', handler));
});
```

### 5. Production monitoring

- Track `process.memoryUsage().heapUsed` as a metric (Prometheus, Datadog, etc.)
- Set alerts at ~70% of `--max-old-space-size`
- Use `--max-old-space-size=<MB>` to make OOMs happen faster and more visibly during testing

